								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נשלמה מלאכת עבודת הקדש זאת ע"י הצעיר <name type="person" role="scribe">שלמה יצ"ו בן המנוח כמ"ה שמואל מרושינה</name> זצ"ל לכבוד והדר המשכיל והנדון כ"מ <name type="person" role="patron">יעקב פוייט</name> יצ"ו פה אסטי כ"ד לחדש מנחם שנת <date calendar="Hebrew">שמ"א</date> לפ"ק פרש' כי עם קדוש אתה לה'.<locus n="310v"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<support>Paper.</support>
								<extent>310 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>260</height>
										<width>195</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>165</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>310 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained.</p>
									<p>Slightly water-damaged.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="33" writtenLines="33">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
									<p>Initial words and divine names given in larger square characters. </p>
									<p>Additions and corrections given in the margin.</p>
									<p>Lacunae in the text indicated by blank spaces.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian cursive of the 16th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shelomoh ben Shemu῾el of Rossina</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 310v. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p/>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Ya῾aḳov ben Mordekhai Pogeṭṭi</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 310v.</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Boniforte del Asinary</name>: Italian censor (active 1575-1599 in <name type="place">Asti</name>): inscribed with his name: 'Visto et coretto per me Boniforte del Asinari: inscribed (folio 310v).</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Hieronimus Carolus</name>: inscribed with his name: 'Fr. Hier. Carolus Asti Die 19 Febr. <date calendar="Gregorian">1582</date>': inscribed (folio 310v).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Pre-1600. Dark brown leather, blind-tooled, with remains of clasps. Boxed.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Sefer Hap-Peliah. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 26,949.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
